# Source Code Rules

## Real Methods Policy

**Always use real methods and implementations - no mocks, stubs, or fake methods.**

### Implementation Standards
- All functions use real library implementations
- All file operations use real file system operations (pathlib, os, etc.)
- All validation uses real validation logic
- All API integrations use real API clients (requests, etc.)

### Module Structure
- Each module follows consistent structure: `__init__.py`, `main.py`, `utils.py`, `config.py`
- All modules are self-contained with clear boundaries
- Minimal dependencies between modules

### Code Quality
- Type hints for all functions
- Comprehensive docstrings
- Error handling with appropriate exceptions
- Modular, reusable code

### Dependencies
- Use real library implementations only
- No mock or stub libraries
- Proper error handling for external dependencies
- Clear documentation of external service requirements
